# 🌡️ Reading an Analog Temperature Sensor with Arduino

In this example, the Arduino reads an analog temperature sensor (such as the **LM35**) through one of its analog input pins.

The program follows a simple workflow:

1. Read the analog sensor value.
2. Convert the ADC value into voltage.
3. Convert the voltage into temperature.
4. Display the result on the Serial Monitor.

---

# Source Code

```cpp
int sensorDeger = 0;
float gerilim = 0;
float sicaklik = 0;

void setup() {
    Serial.begin(9600);
}

void loop() {

    sensorDeger = analogRead(sensorPin);

    gerilim = (sensorDeger / 1024.0) * 5000.0;

